<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634106680030648188" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634305166092575082">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[The example]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>The example&nbsp;contains the Visual WebGui <em>RibbonBar </em>control with two pages: Email and Edit.<br />Each page contains two RibbonBarGroup objects:</p><ul><li>Email page<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; Actions<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; Tools&nbsp;(with advanced anchor)</li><li>Edit page<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; Find and Replace (with advanced anchor)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; IntelliSense</li></ul><p>Switch between pages to see the groups.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement3"><![CDATA[<p>The example demonstrates different types of Items and SubItems available with RibbonBar control out of the box. The <strong>Email</strong> page contains Actions group with four RibbonBarButtonItem objects. The <strong>Tools</strong> page contains single RibbonBarDropDownButton object. Press the buttons to see how it looks when mouse goes over and how event handler works. Press Tools button to see drop down menu, press menu items.</p><p>The second page - Edit is more complex and demonstrates two additional types of Items:</p><ul><li><strong>Find and Replace</strong> is RibbonBarStackItem</li><li><strong>IntelliSense</strong> is RibbonBarFlowItem</li></ul><p>See the article &quot;<em>Object Model Overview</em>&quot; for additional details about different Item&nbsp;types.</p><p>The &quot;Find and Replace&quot; stack item contains three SubItems demonstrating look and feel of:</p><ul><li><em>DropDownButtonItem</em> with associated context menu -&nbsp;<strong>Where</strong></li><li><em>RibbonBarCheckBoxItem -&nbsp;</em><strong>Case Sensitive</strong></li><li><em>RibbonBarButtonItem - &nbsp;</em><strong>Quick Find</strong><em>&nbsp;</em>with image</li></ul><p>The IntelliSense group contains FlowLayoutPanel based container.<br />You can see how look SubItems of:</p><ul><li><em>RibbonBarComboBoxItem</em></li><li><em>RibbonBarTextBoxItem</em></li><li><em>RibbonBarToolBarItem</em> with multiple&nbsp;<em>RibbonBarToolBarButtonItem </em>objects</li></ul><p>Pay attention the&nbsp;RibbonBarFlowItem Width is adjustable (move trackbar to see how it changes the panel width and layout of subitems). Press the button on the right side to return the flow panel to initial state.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[Adding Items in Design time]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>Review &quot;Adding Pages&quot; and &quot;Adding Groups&quot; examples to learn how to add pages and groups.</p><p>To add items to the <em>RibbonBar </em>control, follow these steps:</p><ol><li>Select a page to edit in the RibbonBar Page collection editor.</li><li>Select a group to edit&nbsp;in the&nbsp;RibbonBar Group collection editor.&nbsp;</li><li>Press Add button to add default type or the small arrow to select the type of Item (see image below)</li></ol>]]></Paragraph>
    <Image Code="ImageElement1" Resource="adding items2.png" Type="Resource" />
    <Header Code="HeaderElement3" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[Adding SubItems in Design time]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement4"><![CDATA[<p>To add SubItems to the RibbonBar control, follow these steps:</p><ul><li>Select a page to edit in the RibbonBar Page collection editor.</li><li>Select a group to edit in the RibbonBar Group collection editor.</li><li>Select a stack / flow Item and press Items to open RibbonBar Item Collection Editor</li><li>Press Add button to add default type or the small arrow to select the type of Item (see image below)</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Image Code="ImageElement2" Resource="adding subitems_2.png" Type="Resource" />
    <Header Code="HeaderElement4" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[Enabled, Image, Tag, Tooltip, Text, Visible]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement5"><![CDATA[<p>These properties available for Item and SubItem objects and could be manipulated programmatically to implement application logic.<br />The properties intended to:</p><ul><li><strong>Text </strong>- a text shown under the item as a caption (System.String), not all types of items displays this text</li><li><strong>Tag </strong>- an object associated with item to implement application logic (System.Object), see example&nbsp;rb_ButtonClick() where the Tag used to store the button name</li><li><strong>ToolTip </strong>- a text shown when mouse goes over the item (System.String)</li><li><strong>Visible </strong>- a boolean to determine whether to show or hide the item (System.Boolean)</li><li><strong>Enabled </strong>- a boolean to determine whether the item is responsive to click events (System.Boolean), see example where whole ToolBar - rbSItemBar2&nbsp;with two items was disabled.</li><li><strong>Image </strong>- the property serves to display graphics on the item, use designer to simplify definition or provide valid Gizmox.WebGUI.Common.Resources.IconResourceHandle object programmatically.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>]]></Paragraph>
  </Nodes>
</Data>